wikipedia_page.main: Henry Graham Sharp, known professionally as Graham Sharp (19 December 1917 – 2 January 1995) was a British figure skater. In 1939, he won both the  European Figure Skating Championships and the World Figure Skating Championships. Before that, he had won three consecutive silver medals at Worlds and Europeans. He competed at the 1936 Winter Olympics, where he placed fifth, and at the 1948 Winter Olympics, where he placed seventh.
